About
V Theater is located inside Miracle Mile Shops at Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino and features two showrooms with nine live stage productions including the award winning V - The Ultimate Variety Show a family favorite 17 years running as well as the world's #1 pole dancing class for women, Stripper 101.

    Great talent…. Theater and set, not so much.
    We went to the Carpenter Legacy show, the debut night of the Christmas show. Both of the stars did an amazing job. Really good. My comments are about the actual venue. The theater had an older, sorry, but shabby feel to it. The stage set was disappointing. The piano had fingerprints all over the side of it, the Christmas tree looked like it had seen a better day, etc. The lighting looked very out of date. I wonder how much better this show could be if it just had the feel of something worthy if the talent and the patrons in Vegas who come to see it.
    Visited December 2023
    Traveled with family
    Written December 5, 2023

Fun Time!
Nov 2022 • Couples
We saw two shows on our recent visit to The V theater in Las Vegas. We saw Zombie Burlesque and A Musical about Star Wars. Both shows were fantastic. My husband and I laughed and had an overall good time.

The staff at the theater is so friendly and welcoming. There is a great bar waiting area with a view of the mall. The theater is small/ intimate so any seat is a good seat.

Highly recommend to see these two shows!
